cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
1. cs.RO (Robotics): The paper presents a vision-based route-following system for the safe return of UAVs under primary navigation failure. This involves developing algorithms for visual mapping, localisation, and control of the UAV, which are all core topics in robotics.
2. cs.CV (Computer Vision): The paper heavily relies on computer vision techniques such as stereo vision, visual odometry, and visual localisation to achieve autonomous navigation of the UAV. The paper also discusses the performance of the visual localisation algorithm under different conditions.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper uses a Visual Teach & Repeat framework to build a visual map of the environment and to enable the autonomous return of the UAV. This involves developing AI algorithms for learning and recognition of visual features in the environment.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the closed-loop autonomy of the UAV along a complicated path, which involves developing control algorithms for the UAV to follow the safe outbound path back to the launch point.
5. cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although not a primary focus of the paper, the Visual Teach & Repeat framework used for building the visual map and enabling autonomous return of the UAV involves machine learning techniques for recognition and classification of visual features.
